TSX-V-listed Japan Gold has announced a private placement to raise C$15-million for drilling and advanced exploration at its wholly-owned Ikutahara and Ohra-Takamine projects. The company, which also has an alliance with bullion major Barrick Gold in Japan, will place 42 857 143 shares at C$0.35 each to raise the funds. Japan Gold has 31 gold projects, which cover areas with known gold occurrences. The company’s stock closed at C$0.36 a share on Friday – down 4% on the previous day’s close.